<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 8:58AM CDT  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Kankakee County through 930 AM CDT...
At 857 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Herscher, moving east at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Kankakee, Bourbonnais, Bradley, Herscher, Limestone, Chebanse, Aroma
Park, Bonfield, Buckingham, Sammons Point, Reddick, Irwin and Union
Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
